BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (18): SERBIA (POMORAVLJE), OVINE, SEROTYPE 4, OIE
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 30 Sep 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(40) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21092


Bluetongue, Serbia
------------------
Information received on [and dated] 30 Sep 2016 from Dr Budimir Plavsic, head, Animal Health Department Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture and Environmental Protection, Belgrade, Serbia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 17 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 21 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Dec 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus [BTV]
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (15056): Rekovac, Rekovac, Pomoravski [Pomoravlje], Srbija
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 70 / 4 / 2 / - / -

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed in percentages):
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 5.71 / 2.86 / 50 / **
Sheep / 9.3 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Institute of Veterinary Medicine of Serbia (national laboratory) / Sheep / real-time PCR / 21 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

